  "text": "Another approach for amplifying the thermal expansion is to use geometric constraints that force the actuator to move in the desired direction. An example of this type of amplification is the \"bent beam\" actuator, illustrated in Figure 4 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . As the thin legs heat up, the expansion causes an amplified deflection in the direction shown.",
